# LWC Component Rules

## DO NOT

- Use `class:foo={bar}` attribute directives in templates — not valid in LWC, causes compile failure
- Put `role="tablist"` on a list whose items have no `role="tab"`, `aria-selected`, or keyboard handling
- Render a custom modal without `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, and `aria-labelledby`
- Make rename/edit interactions discoverable only via `ondblclick` — always provide a keyboard-accessible trigger
- Call `JSON.parse` or a helper that parses the same prop more than once per render cycle — parse once, pass through
- Surface raw debug output (char codes, JSON repr, per-column details) in user-facing error messages

## Template Syntax

### Class bindings — use computed strings, not `class:` directives

```html
<!-- GOOD -->
<div class={row.rowClass}></div>   <!-- rowClass computed in JS getter -->

<!-- BAD — compile error -->
<div class:selected={row.isSelected}></div>
```

Build class strings in the JS getter (e.g., `visibleRows`) using string concatenation:

```js
rowClass: 'tree-row' + (isSelected ? ' tree-row-selected' : '')
```

## Accessibility

### Modal dialogs

Every custom modal overlay must have:

```html
<div class="modal-card"
     role="dialog"
     aria-modal="true"
     aria-labelledby="my-modal-title">
    <h2 id="my-modal-title">Modal Title</h2>
    ...
</div>
```

- Set initial focus to the first interactive element or the dialog itself on open
- Trap focus within the modal while it is open

### Step indicators / progress trackers

Use a plain `<ol>` or `<ul>` with `aria-label`:

```html
<!-- GOOD -->
<ul class="step-indicator" aria-label="Wizard steps">

<!-- BAD — tablist requires interactive tab children -->
<ul class="step-indicator" role="tablist">
```

### Interactive controls

Every custom button or control that isn't a native `<button>` needs:
- `aria-label` describing the action (not just a title attribute)
- `aria-expanded` (string `'true'`/`'false'`) if it toggles a region
- Keyboard handler (`onkeydown`) supporting at minimum Enter/Space

### Rename / edit actions

If a node can be renamed, always provide both:
1. A `lightning-button-icon` (or equivalent) that fires the rename handler — keyboard reachable
2. The existing `ondblclick` shortcut for mouse users

```html
<lightning-button-icon
    icon-name="utility:edit"
    alternative-text="Rename"
    title="Rename"
    data-path={row.path}
    onclick={handleRenameClick}
></lightning-button-icon>
```

## Performance

### Parse JSON once per render

When a getter calls a parse helper (`_pathCounts()`, `JSON.parse(...)`) and a sub-method also calls it, pass the parsed result as a parameter rather than re-parsing:

```js
// GOOD
get visibleRows() {
    const pathCounts = this._pathCounts();                          // parse once
    const metrics = this._buildMetrics(pathCounts);                // pass through
    ...
}
_buildMetrics(pathCounts = null) {
    if (!pathCounts) pathCounts = this._pathCounts();              // fallback for standalone calls
    ...
}

// BAD — parses productCountsJson twice per render
get visibleRows() {
    const pathCounts = this._pathCounts();
    const metrics = this._buildMetrics();                          // calls _pathCounts() again internally
}
```

### CSV / hierarchy path — avoid redundant parsing

When a CSV path already re-parses `hierarchyJson` internally, do not call `parseParentsList()` as a gate first:

```js
// GOOD — countCsvLines handles empty hierarchy itself
if (csvImportData) {
    newFromHierarchy = countCsvImportLines(hierarchyJson, csvImportData);
} else {
    const parents = parseParentsList(hierarchyJson);
    if (parents?.length) newFromHierarchy = sumProductCounts(productCountsJson);
}
```

## Error Messages

User-facing error messages must be **concise and actionable** — no raw file content, char codes, or JSON representations:

```js
// GOOD
out.error = 'Invalid CSV header. Expected: ' + EXPECTED_HEADER + '. Check that the file was not modified.';

// BAD — exposes file internals, overwhelms the user
out.error = 'Invalid header.\n--- DEBUG ---\nRaw line: ' + JSON.stringify(rawLine) + '\nChar codes: ' + codes.join(',') + ...;
```

Log debug details to `console.error` only, not the UI.
